From 891ebfe73b01e23a67f7d5556e28cd2829b4bfdc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Richard Gibbs <wofderfs@googlemail.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 23:43:39 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 10/10] GUI defaults: a Swing app runs with zero flags

classlibDefaultBootClassPath gains amigatoolkit.zip (the sun.awt.amiga
toolkit, flat-relative like the rest), and classlibAddDefaultProperties sets
awt.toolkit=sun.awt.amiga.AmigaToolkit +
java.awt.graphicsenv=sun.awt.amiga.AmigaGraphicsEnvironment (command-line -D
still overrides; a missing zip is skipped harmlessly and only matters when
AWT is actually touched).

Canonical GUI launch is now identical to headless:
    jamvm-openjdk -cp app.jar Main

Verified on qemu-java: zero-flag SwingTest passes fully (window + action
pipeline + clean exit); zero-flag headless HelloWorld regression unaffected.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
